intltool
------------------------------------------
The intltool collection can be used to do these things:

 o Extract translatable strings from various source files (.xml.in,
   .glade, .desktop.in, .server.in, .oaf.in).

 o Collect the extracted strings together with messages from traditional
   source files (.c, .h) in po/$(PACKAGE).pot.

 o Merge back the translations from .po files into .xml, .desktop and
   .oaf files.  This merge step will happen at build resp. installation
   time.

The intltool package has a script, intltoolize, which copies the various
scripts and does the other magic to your module. So users building
from tarballs don't need intltool, only folks building from cvs.
(This is modelled on gettextize.)

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  bash
  perl-5.8.7-5

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-2
  cygport-0.2.10-1
  gawk-3.1.5-4
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.gnome.org/

Canonical download:
  ftp://ftp.gnome.org/pub/gnome/sources/intltool/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack intltool-0.35.5-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./intltool-0.35.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/intltool-0.35.5-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/intltool-0.35.5-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

